SEMDL Help Topic: reference remove

Usage:
- `ssd remove <selector> <file>`
- `ssd remove type:<kind> --allow-multi <file>`

Purpose:
- Remove one sidecar metadata field or subtree when the selector resolves safely.
- Structural multi-target and reference-breaking removals still fail.

Related help:
- `ssd help grammar`
- `ssd help recipes wrong-layer`

Sample:
- `ssd remove meta:A1.embedding docs/examples/minimal.ssd`
